message.content: We notice that $(n-3)(n-8)=n^2-11n+24$. The quadratic is $0$ when $n=3$ or $n=8$, so the quadratic changes sign at $n=3$ and $n=8$. We want the quadratic to be less than or equal to $0$, which means it has to be non-positive. Since the quadratic changes sign at $n=3$ and $n=8$, the quadratic is negative when $3\leq n\leq 8$, so the greatest integer $n$ that satisfies $n^2 - 11n +24 \leq 0$ is $\boxed{8}$.
